Regarding thought notes from Mr Gabhart:
Altho I have not seen many samples of QuikSkript from others, the few I
have seen required a bit more study than my own script. I would be
curious however, to ask others in the group what their experience would
be regarding the readability of both scripts. From my lights, I was
thinking that just as roman handwriting is individualistic, so would be
the Read scripts. Of course, if one is conscious about a common
pronounciation and a common script then it would seem that there would
be no problem. But again, as we become fluent in a script, individual
characteristics creep in. Roman script for example, is so variable due
to personality characteristics and so it seems that the same problem
would crop up in Read&#39;s script as well. How many of you out there are
experienced in reading the scripts of others -- please enlighten those
who have the curiosity of the cat.
Sid


